description: Actor Nagarjuna Akkineni's N-Convention Centre was demolished by the newly-formed Hyderabad Disaster Response and Assets Monitoring and Protection Agency (HYDRA) on Saturday for allegedly encroaching on Tummidikunta lake's area. Despite Nagarjuna's claims of the action being unlawful, the High Court ordered a stay on further demolition. The property is co-owned by Nagarjuna and N Preetham.
title: Actor's convention centre in Hyderabad razed for 'encroachment'

description: Rahul Gandhi reaffirmed his demand for a caste census, highlighting its necessity for policy changes to benefit marginalized communities. Gandhi noted the lack of representation of OBCs, SCs, and STs in key sectors, including corporate, judiciary, and media.
title: Caste census must to benefit 90% of excluded people: Rahul

description: In a surprising show of solidarity, SP chief Akhilesh Yadav defended BSP supremo Mayawati after BJP MLA Rajesh Chaudhary called her "the most corrupt chief minister of UP ever" during a debate. Akhilesh criticized the remark as "deplorable" and called for a defamation suit. Mayawati expressed gratitude, leading to speculation about a possible reconciliation between their parties.
title: Akhilesh springs to Mayawati's defence, sparks speculation

description: India and the US enhanced their major defence partnership to support a free and open Indo-Pacific, addressing key regional security issues. Defence Minister Rajnath Singh and US National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan discussed defence collaboration projects and potential industrial cooperation. This followed Singh's talks with US Defence Secretary Lloyd J Austin on strengthening bilateral initiatives amid China's expansionist behavior.
title: Will work to deepen defence ties: Pentagon after Rajnath Singh's visit

description: BJP and INLD requested the Election Commission to defer the Oct 1 assembly polls in Haryana, citing concerns over low voter turnout due to an extended holiday weekend. BJP's Mohanlal Badoli and INLD's Abhay Chautala pointed out that many voters might miss the election. Congress leaders criticized the request, claiming it was due to BJP's fear of defeat.
title: BJP cites long weekend, says defer October 1 Haryana assembly election

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah urged for a decisive end to left-wing extremism by March 2026, highlighting successes in states like Bihar, Jharkhand, and Chhattisgarh. Shah praised Chhattisgarh's efforts, noting significant arrests and surrenders of Maoists. He encouraged Maoists to adopt a new surrender policy to establish the rule of law in affected areas.
title: March 2026 target to end Naxal menace: Union minister Amit Shah

description: In Assam's Nagaon district, a suspect in the gang rape of a Class 10 student drowned while attempting to escape police custody during a crime scene re-enactment. The incident has sparked public outrage and calls for strong action. Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma emphasized a zero-tolerance policy towards crimes against women, vowing quick apprehension of remaining suspects.
title: Zero-tolerance policy for crimes against women in Assam: CM

description: The CBI conducted a polygraph test on Sandip Ghosh, former principal of RG Kar Medical College, in connection with the rape-murder of a postgraduate resident doctor. Tests will follow for six others including prime suspect Sanjay Roy. A team from New Delhi conducted the tests after court approval. The CBI aims to verify statements and investigate leads for the case.
title: Ex-principal Sandip Ghosh undergoes CBI polygraph test, Roy's turn next
Telegram CEO Pavel Durov arrested in France: Reports

description: The central government announced a revamp of the National Pension System, benefiting 23 lakh employees by guaranteeing a 50% payout of the average basic pay for the last 12 months of service. The new Unified Pension Scheme will offer inflation adjustments and higher government contributions, addressing concerns over market fluctuations and aligning benefits with the old pension scheme.
title: Centre nods for UPS, assures 50% of basic pay as pension

description: The Union Cabinet approved the BioE3 biotech policy and unified the three schemes into 'Vigyan Dhara' with an outlay of over Rs 10,579 crore. BioE3 aims to promote high-performance biomanufacturing and support India's net zero emission goal by 2070. The policy targets technology development, job creation, and sustainable growth while addressing climate change and food security.
title: Policy on high-performance biomanufacturing gets approval

description: The government approved the Unified Pension Scheme for central employees, reinforcing its commitment to their welfare and financial security. Amit Shah and other senior BJP leaders praised the move, highlighting its benefits to employees and their families. The decision was viewed as a significant step towards enhancing the social security of government employees.
title: Amit Shah, Rajnath Singh lead BJP netas in hailing move

description: The Cabinet's approval of UPS provided a significant boost to central government employees, as stated by Joint Consultative Machinery (JCM) representatives who met with PM Narendra Modi. The JCM chief also pushed for revising the minimum wage and lifting the ban on new job posts in government departments, including the railways.
title: Hike minimum monthly wage to Rs 32,500, says government staff body

description: Pakistan had invited PM Modi and other SCO leaders to the Council of Heads of Govt meeting in October, which Modi is unlikely to attend. Due to recent tensions, he may deputize a minister instead. The Indian government has yet to decide on the invite, considering the troubled relationship with Pakistan and recent terror attacks.
title: Pakistan invites PM Modi for SCO CHG meet, he is likely to skip

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister M.K. Stalin emphasized that the Dravidian model of governance respects all faiths and strives for overall development. During the virtual inauguration of the Global Muthamizh Murugan Conference at Palani, he highlighted extensive development work at Murugan temples, including educational initiatives benefiting nearly 4,000 students with free breakfast and planned free lunch.
title: Stalin counters BJP Ram campaign with Murugan fest

description: Nagashree PR, who suffered vision loss in her right eye from the Rameshwaram Cafe blast, regained 80% of her vision after multiple surgeries at Nethradhama Super Specialty Eye Hospital. The procedures included corneal transplantation and retinal surgery. Dr Sri Ganesh highlighted the challenges and risks involved. Nagashree remains hopeful for her daughter's future.
title: Bengaluru cafe blast victim regains 80% vision

description: The BJP had expected political gains from government employees after promising a pension scheme matching 50% of salaries and inflation adjustments, countering Congress's old pension scheme promise. Recent state polls showed mixed reactions. The newly announced Unified Pension Scheme came ahead of upcoming elections, backed by promises of funding and intergenerational equity.
title: With UPS, BJP hopes to win back govt staff it lost to Congress

description: A recent report by 'Prajatantra' showed that 61% of MPs in the 18th Lok Sabha had assets over Rs 5 crores, and 32% came from dynastic backgrounds. The analysis indicated that local and party organizational politics were common non-privileged entry pathways. Only 8.1% of MPs defied monetary, dynastic, and criminal entry barriers.
title: 61% Lok Sabha MPs possess assets of Rs 5 crore and above, says report

description: The Islamic State claimed responsibility for a knife attack in Solingen, Germany, that killed three people during the city's 650th anniversary festival. The attacker targeted Christians in retaliation for the treatment of Muslims. Authorities conducted raids and arrested a teenager for withholding information. Investigations are ongoing, as the government pledges support to the affected city.
title: Islamic State claims responsibility for Germany's knife attack

description: Following India's first National Space Day, Tamil Nadu-based Space Zone India launched the country's inaugural reusable hybrid rocket, Mission RHUMI-2024, from Chennai. The rocket, equipped with a hybrid motor and parachute deployer, carried Cube and PICO satellites aiming to collect data on global warming. The initiative highlights India's advancements in cost-effective and eco-friendly space technologies.
title: TN-based space startup launches India’s first reusable hybrid rocket

description: Kamala Harris has a whole segment under 'Cooking with Kamala' in her YouTube channel and clips from those videos never fail to amaze social media users as Vice President Kamala Harris is readying for the presidential race. Recently, a video of her cracking open an egg in one hand went viral as social media users want to take up this method as a challenge.
title: Kamala Harris can crack open an egg in one hand. Internet is impressed

description: India aimed to double its Female Labour Force Participation Rate to 70% by 2047 to become a $30 trillion economy. Achieving this target required approximately 400 million women in the workforce. To hit these marks, urgent measures were required to support women and ensure their contribution to economic growth, acknowledged by The/Nudge Institute's report.
title: How many workforce of women India need to become USD 30 tln economy by 2047

description: The BJP emphasized its commitment to protecting reservation policies for marginalized communities in J&K, countering the Congress-NC alliance's pledge to revise these policies if elected. The alliance also vowed to restore J&K’s statehood and political status before Article 370 was revoked in 2019. Legal experts questioned the assembly's power to overturn Union government decisions.
title: BJP moves to scuttle Cong-NC pledge to revise post-Art 370 quotas in J&K

description: Mehbooba Mufti, PDP president, announced complete support for the NC-Congress alliance in J&K assembly polls, provided they accept her party's agenda of resolving the Kashmir issue. Releasing PDP's manifesto, she ruled out any post-poll alliance with BJP and emphasized addressing J&K's human issues, restoring its statehood, and lifting bans on certain organizations and laws.
title: Mehbooba vows to back Congress-NC alliance if they accept ‘PDP agenda’

description: In Sopore area of north Kashmir's Baramulla district, a terrorist was killed and a soldier injured during a brief firefight, ensuing from a joint naka checking. Authorities seized a pistol, grenades, and ammunition from the site. Reinforcements secured the area, aiming to ensure smooth upcoming assembly elections amid heightened security measures.
title: Terrorist killed, soldier injured in Sopore gunfight
Astronauts Sunita Williams, Butch Wilmore to return to Earth in February 2025: Nasa

description: Union home minister Amit Shah, during his visit to Raipur, urged for a decisive end to left-wing extremism by March 2026. He highlighted the progress made in reducing Maoist influence in various states due to strategic development and security measures. Shah emphasized the importance of cooperation between states and the successful implementation of government policies to achieve this goal.
title: Time has come for ruthless, final blow to finish Maoists by 2026: Amit Shah

description: Former Indian men's cricket team opener, Shikhar Dhawan announced his retirement from international cricket on Saturday, drawing curtains upon his career spanning over a decade and 269 matches, where he scored 10,867 runs at an average close to 40.
title: Shikhar Dhawan: What will 'Gabbar' be remembered for in world of cricket?

description: On August 26, 2024, India celebrated Krishna Janmashtami, marking Lord Krishna's 5251st birth anniversary. The festival included fasting, rituals, midnight celebrations, and community events. Devotees shared greetings and messages, reflecting on Krishna's teachings and wishing each other joy and prosperity. The nation embraced the occasion with devotion and fervor, honoring Krishna's legacy.
title: Happy Krishna Janmashtami: Wishes, messages, quotes, images & WA status
Vigyan Dhara scheme: Centre approves internships for Class 11 & 12 science, tech students

description: Union minister Ashwini Vaishnaw announced on Saturday that the Union Cabinet, led by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, approved the BioE3 policy to encourage high-performance biomanufacturing. This policy aims to support innovation-driven R&D and entrepreneurship in various sectors, promising a bio-revolution. It aligns with the government's missions like 'Net Zero' carbon economy and emphasizes sustainable growth through 'Circular Bioeconomy.'
title: 'Bio-revolution is coming': What is Centre's new BioE3 policy?

description: Last night’s Friday Night SmackDown delivered high energy and memorable moments. Key highlights included LA Knight’s victory over Santos Escobar, Kevin Owens’ decisive encounter with Grayson Waller, and ongoing tensions within the Bloodline as Jacob Fatu reluctantly relinquished his championship belt to Tonga Loa. Read the full article for more exciting details.
title: 5 best moments from SmackDown (8/23)

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi-led Cabinet has on Saturday approved the Unified Pension Scheme for government employees. The new Unified Pension Scheme will benefit 23 lakh central government employees.
title: Unified Pension Scheme approved by Cabinet, to benefit 23 lakh employees

description: Rahul Gandhi, Congress MP, stated that 90% of the population remains disconnected from the system despite having the necessary skills, stressing the importance of a caste census. He emphasized that this census could provide crucial data for informed policy decisions and ensure benefits reach those in need, particularly focusing on OBCs, Dalits, and workers in various sectors.
title: '90% sitting outside system': Rahul doubles down on caste census demand

description: The Undertaker, WWE Hall of Famer, revealed his initial jitters about his 1990 debut, fearing he would be the Gobbledy Gooker. Called 'The Undertaker' by Vince McMahon, he embraced the role, drawing inspiration from Clint Eastwood westerns. His performances made him an iconic and beloved character in WWE history.
title: 'The old man called me, Is this The Undertaker?'- Superstar shares story

description: Mohammad Rizwan is currently involved in Pakistan's first Test against Bangladesh in Rawalpindi where he scored unbeaten 171 in the first innings. Rizwan's daddy ton helped Pakistan reach 448-6 before declaring their first innings. Bangladesh however came up with a strong reply while batting, responding with 565 all out. Riding on Mushfiqur Rahim's 191, a 93 from Shadman Islam and fifties from Mehidy Hasan Miraz and Litton Das and Mominul Haque, Bangladesh took a 117-run first innings lead on the fourth day of the Test.
title: Rizwan kabootar ki tarah koodta rehta: India umpire

description: The Haryana BJP asked the Election Commission to delay assembly polls scheduled for October 1 due to a series of holidays that might lower voter turnout. The Congress criticized this, suggesting the BJP is fearful of losing the elections. The Chief Electoral Officer forwarded the request to the Election Commission for consideration.
title: Haryana BJP urges EC to defer assembly election; Congress hits back

description: Pakistan pacer spearhead Shaheen Shah Afridi and his wife, Ansha Afridi announced the arrival of their first born, a son they have named Ali Yar.
title: Shaheen Afridi welcomes his newborn son with unique celebration

description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma said that no Hindus have attempted to enter India from Bangladesh in the past month despite instability in the neighboring country. However, 35 Muslim infiltrators, seeking employment in the textile sector in states like Bangalore and Tamil Nadu, have been arrested. He urged the Prime Minister to push Bangladesh to protect its Hindu minority.
title: 'Not coming to India': Assam CM explains why Hindus are staying in Bangladesh

description: Congress criticized the use of "bulldozer action" to demolish the house of an accused during a protest in Madhya Pradesh, labeling it barbaric and unjust. They accused BJP-ruled states of targeting minorities using state machinery and bypassing the judicial process, emphasizing that only courts should deliver justice according to the law and constitution.
title: 'Height of barbarism': Congress attacks bulldozer action in BJP-ruled states
1 terrorist killed in encounter in J&K's Sopore; op still on

description: Mehbooba Mufti, PDP chief, announced that her party would contest the upcoming J&K assembly elections for dignity and permanent resolution, not statehood or seat sharing. She emphasized solving the issue of Jammu and Kashmir and pushed for the restoration of trade with Pakistan. Mufti also announced several social security commitments in the party's manifesto.
title: 'Won't contest if ...': Mehbooba Mufti's message for NC, Cong ahead of J&K polls

description: In a surprising move, Robert Kennedy Jr, a notable independent candidate, suspended his presidential campaign and endorsed Donald Trump. Kennedy's support waned from 15 per cent to 5 per cent after Kamala Harris secured the Democratic nomination. The endorsement's impact on voter dynamics remains uncertain, though Harris's lead over Trump saw only a minor change of 0.2 per cent in one poll.
title: Kamala faces a Kennedy wrinkle on road to Kamalot

description: The Indian Air Force's C-130 J Hercules airlifted the bodies of 25 bus accident victims from Nepal to Jalgaon, Maharashtra. The aircraft with call sign IFC1084, which was dispatched from Panagarh airbase of IAF on the directions of defence minister Rajnath Singh, took off with mortal remains from Bharatpur airport at 5:06 pm and covered the distance of 1604 km to reach Jalgaon airport at 7:12 pm.
title: Nepal bus tragedy: IAF's C-130J Hercules brings home bodies of 25 victims

description: India aimed to add 400 million women to its workforce by 2047, seeking to nearly double the female labour force participation rate to 70%. The/Nudge Institute's report highlighted significant job security disparities, showing women are more likely to lose and not recover jobs. COVID-19 exacerbated employment fragility for rural women, necessitating urgent action and systemic changes.
title: 'India needs 400 million more women in workforce by 2047 to fuel economy'

description: Shikhar Dhawan, 38, said he leaves the scene a content man, having represented the national team in all three formats since making his international debut in 2010 in an ODI against Australia in Visakhapatnam. Dhawan appeared in 34 Tests, 167 ODIs and 68 T20Is for India. His best came in the 50-over format in which he amassed 6793 runs at an average of 44.11. He averaged 40.61 for his 2315 Test runs.
title: Punjab Kings' heartfelt message for Dhawan has touch of Dhoni

description: India batter KL Rahul spoke about the controversy that led to his suspension by the BCCI in 2019. The controversy arose after Rahul and his teammate Hardik Pandya appeared on the well-known television program "Koffee With Karan".
title: 'Never got suspended, punished in school but that interview...': Rahul

description: President Volodymyr Zelenskyy remarked during Ukraine's 33rd Independence Day speech that Russia's military campaign has resulted in conflict spilling into Russian territory. He also emphasized Ukraine's legal progress by ratifying the Rome Statute and signing a law banning Moscow-linked religious groups. Additionally, a drone strike in Russia's Voronezh region caused emergency protocols to be enacted.
title: 'War has returned to Russia': Zelenskyy hails Ukraine offensive in I-Day speech

description: A private helicopter owned by a private aviation company crashed near Paud village in Pune district. The helicopter was en route from Mumbai to Hyderabad with four people onboard. "Among the 4 people who were in the Helicopter, captain sustained injuries and is hospitalised. The rest of the three persons are in stable condition," SP Pankaj Deshmukh of Pune Rural Police said.
title: Private helicopter bound for Hyderabad crashes in Pune's Paud village

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy disclosed that Ukraine's incursion into Russia's Kursk region was part of a larger military-diplomatic operation intended to prevent Russia from capturing Sumy and push for a fair peace. Zelenskyy also discussed Ukraine's economic recovery plans post-war, emphasizing the need for future meetings and India's support to boost Kyiv's economy.
title: 'Op aimed at forcing Moscow ...' : What Zelenskyy told TOI on Ukraine's offensive in Russia's Kursk region

description: A dodgy knee kept bothering MS Dhoni for most of the last Indian Premier League (IPL) season, where the former Chennai Super Kings' skipper was often spotted wearing a knee brace. But the legendary ex-India captain looked fit as a fiddle in a short video clip on social media, where the 43-year-old could be seen on a badminton court, hitting a jump smash at rocket speed.
title: Watch: Dhoni's badminton jump smash is absolute rocket

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah criticized Governor Thaawarchand Gehlot's decision to allow his prosecution in the Mysuru Urban Development Authority (Muda) site allotment scam, labeling it 'unconstitutional'. The High Court has deferred proceedings until the next hearing on August 29. The alleged scam involves compensatory site allotments under a controversial scheme benefiting Siddaramaiah's wife.
title: 'Raj Bhavan misused': Sidda calls governor's prosecution unconstitutional

description: A non-resident Indian, Sukhchain Singh, was shot by two unidentified assailants outside his residence in Amritsar's Daburji village. The attackers, who arrived on a motorcycle, demanded registration documents for Singh's luxury car before shooting him twice. Singh was hospitalized, and police are investigating the incident, which was captured on CCTV. Singh's wife alleges that his first wife's family was involved.
title: NRI shot at by armed assailants at his residence in Amritsar
Watch: Greek-flagged oil tanker goes up in flames after Houthi attack

description: Shikhar Dhawan, known for his selflessness and tenacity, has retired from all forms of cricket. Presented with the Test cap by Sachin Tendulkar, Dhawan's career, highlighted by his 2013 Champions Trophy performance, was marked by consistency in ODIs and significant contributions in Tests. Despite setbacks, he remained dignified and supportive of his team.
title: 'We know about your...': When Tendulkar presented Dhawan India Test cap

description: YouTube CEO Neal Mohan recently visited India for the company's Brandcast event, celebrating the influence of Indian creators. He mentioned the substantial growth of YouTube Shorts in India, which has now achieved trillions of views. Mohan also highlighted that India has over 11,000 creators with more than a million subscribers each, emphasizing their global impact.
title: YouTube CEO shares photo in front of India Gate: 'The visit was even...'

description: Having announced his retirement on Saturday after an international career of over a decade, former India opening batsman Shikhar Dhawan relived the memories he made during his successful stint in the India jersey, including a prolific six-year period that is dear to him. He went on to thank all those who made a difference in her career.
title: Dhawan cherishes 6 years & 100 tons with Virat & Rohit

description: Following a sexual assault against two minors in Thane district, NCP-SCP chief criticized Maharashtra's government for insensitivity and inaction. He participated in a silent protest and condemned dismissive responses by the government. The incident led to outrage and protests despite a court ban, demanding justice for the victims and challenging Maharashtra's reputation nationwide.
title: Badlapur incident hit image of Maharashtra in the country: Sharad Pawar

description: A tussle ensued between BRS and Congress women workers in New Delhi after former Telangana minister KT Rama Rao visited the women's commission office regarding his alleged remarks on women. Congresswomen demanded an apology from KTR. Although KTR had previously issued an apology for his comments, tensions remained high during the confrontation.
title: BRS & Congress workers clash over KTR's 'brake dance' remark

description: From a second-ball duck on his India debut in an ODI against Australia in 2010 to forming one of India's most formidable opening partnerships with Rohit Sharma and becoming India's man of the moment in ICC tournaments, Dhawan has had a successful career in the India jersey. Here's a look at the highlights of his career.
title: Dhawan retires with a record of his yet to be broken

description: Uddhav Thackeray, along with family and party leaders, protested outside Shiv Sena-UBT headquarters in Dadar against the Badlapur sexual abuse case. The MVA leaders, including Sharad Pawar and Nana Patole, also held protests across Maharashtra. The accused were arrested after a delay in police action, sparking statewide demonstrations and disruptions to train services.
title: Badlapur assault: Shiv Sena (UBT), NCP protest wearing black bands

description: Yuri Kawaguchi, a 29-year-old Tokyo news anchor and harassment prevention lecturer, was terminated after criticizing men's hygiene in a viral social media post. Despite apologizing, she faced severe backlash and lost her job. The incident spurred debate about gender expectations and societal norms in Japan, reflecting the challenges women face in a male-dominated society.
title: Japanese TV anchor loses job after criticising men body odour

description: Australian workers gained the right to ignore work-related contact outside designated hours under new legislation effective from Monday. Passed in February, the law allows employees to disconnect without repercussions unless deemed unreasonable. This move aligns with similar policies in parts of Europe. Opposition labeled the law as rushed but acknowledged exceptions based on role and contact reasons.
title: Australia allows workers to 'ignore their bosses after work hours'

description: Meghan Markle's former Toronto home, where she lived while filming Suits and first dated Prince Harry, is now for sale for $1.9 million. Recently renovated with high-end finishes, this three-bedroom house also holds fond memories of Prince Harry's visits. Meghan relocated to London in 2017, and the couple now resides in California.
title: Meghan Markle’s Toronto home from her Suits days now up for sale. See photos

description: Dhawan, who made his international debut in an ODI against Australia in Visakhapatnam in 2010, expressed his satisfaction with his career, having represented India across all three formats. The left-handed opener, who represented India in 34 Tests, 167 ODIs and 68 T20Is, formed a formidable partnership with Rohit Sharma at the top of the India's batting order.
title: 'I see a new world' - says Dhawan after announcing retirement

description: The US government approved the sale of anti-submarine warfare sonobuoys worth $52.8 million to India for its MH-60R Seahawk helicopters. This sale aims to bolster India's ASW capabilities, enhancing its ability to detect and counter threats in the Indian Ocean. The new equipment will complement India's induction of 24 Seahawks by next year.
title: 'Hunter-killer’ helicopters: US approves sonobuoys sale to India

description: The demolition of Hyderabad's N Convention Center, owned by actor Nagarjuna, began after claims of illegal construction on Tammidi Cheruvu land. Reports indicate the center encroached on three and a half acres of the lake. This action follows an investigation into the extent of the encroachment initiated by local authorities.
title: Actor Nagarjuna's Convention Center faces demolition

description: The article delves into Mumtaz and Rajesh Khanna's on-screen chemistry and working relationship in Bollywood. Mumtaz reminisced about their successful collaborations and shared anecdotes about Rajesh Khanna's occasionally moody nature. Despite some challenges, their professional bond resulted in ten box office hits, leaving a lasting legacy in Indian cinema.
title: Did you know Rajesh Khanna got upset with Mumtaz for...?

description: India's first reusable hybrid rocket, 'RHUMI-1', launched successfully from Chennai by Space Zone India and Martin Group. This rocket carried 50 PICO satellites and three Cube satellites. Its hybrid motor uses a safe design, combining propellants during combustion. The previous launch failed due to deployment issues but was resolved this time.
title: Watch: India launches 'RHUMI-1' first reusable hybrid rocket

description: Opener Shikhar Dhawan, who retired from international and domestic cricket, was known for scoring big in ICC tournaments. Debuting under MS Dhoni in 2013 and flourishing under Virat Kohli, Dhawan hit a memorable 117 against Australia in the 2019 ODI World Cup. However, a thumb injury cut his World Cup participation short, and he was replaced by Rishabh Pant.
title: Watch: When Dhawan hit 117 vs Australia with a fractured thumb

description: Former Amazon vice president Ethan Evans recounted working with unethical leaders, highlighting a CEO seducing his wife in retaliation for workplace pushback. Evans advised people to identify and avoid dishonest managers while maintaining integrity and high performance. He shared that staying too long in a toxic environment can have severe personal and professional costs.
title: Ex-Amazon VP on 'bad bosses' and how 'a CEO seduced his wife'

description: Prince Harry, the Duke of Sussex, has been described as an "angry boy" living in America by a close friend. Over four years in the US, Harry is reportedly missing friends and admiration he received in the UK. His controversial public projects have strained relationships, and Harry admits to feeling the loss of old connections.
title: Is Prince Harry growing angry and frustrated in US? Here's what his friends have to say

description: TOI reported on an al-Qaeda network found in Sare Kalan village, Bhiwadi's Chopanki area. Delhi police arrested six suspects after searching the area for over 7 hours. Weapons including an AK-47 rifle and training equipment were recovered. Local residents were surprised, having noticed no suspicious activity. Rajasthan police assured there's no state threat.
title: Discovery of al-Qaeda terrorist module shocks quiet village in Rajasthan

description: Union defence minister Rajnath Singh met US National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and US Secretary of Defence Lloyd Austin to discuss strategic issues and strengthen defence cooperation. Singh engaged with US defence companies at a USISPF roundtable, promoting collaboration under India's Make in India program to achieve self-reliance in the defence sector.
title: Rajnath discusses 'key' strategic matters with US NSA Jake Sullivan
Bengaluru CEO flexes her ‘Brahmin genes', how social media reacted

description: Justin Bieber and Hailey Bieber joyfully welcomed their first child, announcing the arrival of their baby named Jack Blues Bieber on Instagram. The couple, who shared their pregnancy news in May, expressed immense happiness and gratitude. Hailey explained she chose to publicly reveal her pregnancy to enjoy the experience fully.
title: Justin Beiber and Hailey Beiber welcome their first child

description: A 27-year-old woman was arrested for physically abusing her two minor stepsons in Vasai, which included burning their private parts. The children's father, who filed the complaint, noticed injury marks and behavioral changes in his sons. The abuse had been ongoing since the woman married their father, escalating in June.
title: Burned private parts: Woman tortures stepsons over household chores
Badlapur protest: Wife of NCP leader listed as absconding in FIR

description: Apple planned to reveal its latest iPhone models, Apple Watches, and AirPods on September 10, according to Bloomberg. The iPhone 16 lineup was expected to include a new 'Capture Button' and AI-enhanced performance. Larger displays were anticipated for the Pro versions, and the Apple Watch Series 10 and new AirPods models were also expected to debut.
title: When iPhone 16, new AirPods and Apple Watch models may launch?

description: The National Board of Examinations in Medical Sciences (NBEMS) has announced the results for the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test-Postgraduate (NEET PG) 2024 on its official website. The results have been released in PDF format. Candidates can visit  the official website, i.e.,  natboard.edu.in to check and download their respective NEET PG  2024 results.
title: NEET PG 2024 result declared: Check direct link here

description: A New Delhi court allowed the CBI to conduct polygraph tests on seven individuals, including suspect Sanjay Roy, in the RG Kar rape and murder case. Roy agreed to the test, claiming innocence and believing it would exonerate him. Previously, investigators cited evidence against him, including injuries, CCTV footage, and disturbing content found on his phone.
title: Kolkata horror: Why Sanjay Roy gave consent for lie-detector test

description: Two bike-borne assailants opened fire at Singla's Sweets shop in Delhi's Tilak Nagar area late Friday night. No injuries were reported. The police recovered four empty cartridges, and an FIR has been filed. Multiple teams have been formed to investigate and track the assailants' route. The case remains under investigation.
title: Two bike-borne assailants open fire at sweets shop in Delhi

description: An 18-year-old BBA student was assaulted and verbally abused by her senior and his three friends at a suburban railway station after she repeatedly rejected his friendship proposal. Despite the incident occurring in a crowded area, no one intervened until a woman passerby called the police. The police registered an FIR and arrested the four assailants.
title: Senior molests BBA student over rejection of friendship

description: The main accused in the Assam rape case died after jumping into a pond while trying to escape police custody. Police recovered his body after two hours. The incident occurred during a re-creation of the crime scene. The accused was among three who gang-raped a 14-year-old girl in Nagaon district. CM Himanta Biswa Sarma had vowed to bring the perpetrators to justice
title: Assam rape accused falls into pond while trying to flee; dies

description: The CID's Special Investigation Team filed a preliminary chargesheet against former JD(S) MP Prajwal Revanna and his father HD Revanna. They were accused of sexually harassing a domestic help, with allegations including rape and misuse of technology. The chargesheet is yet to be accepted by the special court for elected representatives in Bengaluru.
title: SIT files chargesheet against Prajwal Revanna, his father HD Revanna

description: Shikhar Dhawan has officially announced his retirement from all formats of cricket, effectively concluding a remarkable career that spanned 269 international matches across Tests, ODIs, and T20Is. The left-handed batsman shared his decision through a video posted on X (formerly Twitter), which prompted an outpouring of affection and support from his dedicated fans.
title: 'We'll miss you gabbar': Reactions to Dhawan's retirement

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar addressed concerns raised by foreign reporters over Prime Minister Modi's recent diplomatic visits to Russia and Ukraine. Addressing a question by a BBC reporter who claimed that many were "very upset" to see the interaction between PM Modi and Putin, Jaishankar highlighted the "cultural differences" between the West and the East.
title: 'May not be part of your culture ... ': Jaishankar to reporter on PM Modi-Putin hug

description: Over 100 employees at Google DeepMind urged the company to end military contracts, citing ethical concerns. They highlighted the use of AI for warfare, specifically mentioning Google's Project Nimbus with the Israeli military. The signatories emphasized that such actions conflict with Google's AI Principles. As of August 2024, Google has not meaningfully responded to their concerns.
title: 100s of employees want Google to stop working on these contracts

description: Actress Payel Mukherjee claimed she was attacked by a man on a bike in Kolkata after her car touched his two-wheeler. The man shattered her car window when she refused to get out. Police quickly intervened, arresting the attacker. BJP criticized West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee, alleging deteriorating safety for women in the state. Reacting to the incident, DCP South Kolkata said the accused person has been arrested from the spot.
title: 'Happened amid women's safety rallies .. ': Bengali actress attacked in Kolkata
Beep... beep: Trump rants on Fox, punches phone buttons
'A never Trump guy': A Vance remix goes viral

description: Shikhar Dhawan, a prominent figure in Indian cricket, declared his retirement from international and domestic cricket on Saturday through a video message shared on his social media accounts. The left-handed opener, who made his debut against Australia in Visakhapatnam in 2010, had a successful career spanning over a decade. Throughout his tenure, Dhawan represented India in 34 Tests, 167 ODIs, and 68 T20Is, accumulating more than 10,000 runs across all formats. His remarkable achievements include scoring 24 centuries, with 17 in ODIs and 7 in Tests, showcasing his prowess as a top-order batsman.
title: Shikhar Dhawan announces retirement from international cricket

description: Shigeru Ishiba, former Japanese defence minister, announced his candidacy for the Liberal Democratic Party leadership election set for September 27. This vote will decide the successor to Prime Minister Fumio Kishida. Ishiba supported gradually raising interest rates to normalise Japan's monetary policy, aiming to lower prices and boost industrial competitiveness, following Kishida's decision to step down.
title: Ishiba announces bid to succeed Kishida as Japan's leader

description: The parents of a 31-year-old doctor from R G Kar Medical College expressed frustration over the lack of progress in the CBI's probe into their daughter's rape and murder. They urged the agency to expedite the investigation while also requesting the administration to combat fake news and derogatory social media posts about their daughter.
title: 'Don’t make her tool for business, been 14 days': Kol victim's parents
Mpox: 50-bed isolation ward ready in Bengaluru

description: The Bengaluru Blasters and Hubli Tigers' Maharaja Trophy match etched its name in the annals of cricket history when the game required three Super Overs to determine a winner, an unprecedented occurrence in the sport. Led by Manish Pandey, the Hubli Tigers emerged victorious against Mayank Agarwal's Bengaluru Blasters after the standard 20 overs and two Super Overs failed to break the deadlock between the two teams.
title: Epic cricket clash! 3 Super Overs required to find winner

description: PM Modi on Friday delivered four BHISHM Cubes to Ukraine. These mobile hospital prototypes, developed post-pandemic, can provide emergency medical aid to over 200 persons and set up a functional medical unit within 10 minutes. The initiative aims at expediting treatment for the injured and saving precious lives in disaster situations.
title: PM gifts war-hit Ukraine 4 mobile hospital units to facilitate speedy treatment

description: Mahendra Singh Dhoni, celebrated for his unflappable composure during cricket matches, harbors an intense affection for motorcycles that rivals his dedication to the sport. His enthusiasm for two-wheeled machines is common knowledge among his supporters and cricketing peers. Dhoni's impressive motorcycle collection spans from vintage classics to cutting-edge superbikes, reflecting his diverse tastes.
title: MS Dhoni signs fan's bike in a heartwarming gesture

description: The MVA called off its statewide bandh over the Badlapur school sexual abuse case following a Bombay HC order citing economic loss and essential service disruption. Instead of a total bandh, MVA leaders planned to wear black badges and hold sit-in protests. The HC's decision followed concerns raised in two PILs about possible adverse effects on citizens and businesses.
title: Bandh will hit normal life, no party shall enforce it: Bombay High Court

description: A Kolkata special court approved a polygraph test for Sanjay Roy, accused of raping and killing a trainee doctor at RG Kar Medical College. The court also permitted lie-detection tests on the former principal and four doctors. Evidence, including CCTV footage, linked Roy to the crime scene.
title: Kolkata rape-murder case: Court allows polygraph test on main accused

description: The Calcutta High Court assigned the CBI to investigate corruption charges against RG Kar Medical College's ex-principal Sandip Ghosh, citing the need for a single agency to handle all related allegations. The court sought the transfer of all documents from the SIT by Saturday and directed CBI to report progress by September 17.
title: Probe graft charges against RG Kar ex-principal: Kolkata HC to CBI
